{"TopicId":138126,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"UI Scale breaks map mode.","CreatedByName":"lethalparadox0","CreatedById":144385,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-26T00:00:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"lethalparadox0","CreatedById":144385,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-26T00:00:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I just launched my first vessel of 1.1 into orbit and noticed my apoapsis and periapsis indicators weren\u0027t aligned with the orbit. Upon further investigation I realized none of the planet or moon\u0027s map indicators were in the right spot.\u00A0I don\u0027t believe that any mods broke it but since I have a modded install I\u0027ll post here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere are the mods I currently have:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nContract Configurator\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVarious Contract Packs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDMagic Orbital Science\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDocking Port Alignment Indicator\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinal Frontier\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKAS\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKCT\u00A0(1.3.3-pre2)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKIS\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbal Konstructs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKRASH\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMission Controller 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModular Rocket Systems\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModule\u00A0Manager\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSCANsat\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpacetuxSA\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpaceY Heavy Lifters\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStageRecovery\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToolbar\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTriggerAu Flags\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWaypoint Manager\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt 120% UI Scale nothing is broken:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103589\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EApoapsis and Periapsis\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103597\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMoons\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103617\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EOther Planets\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut at 100% and 80% UI Scale for example things begin to break:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n100% UI:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103663\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EApoapsis and periapsis\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103681\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMoons\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103713\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EPlanets\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103700\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EPlanets\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n80% UI:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103750\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EApoapsis and periapsis\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103766\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMoons\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103796\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EPlanets\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=673103815\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EPlanets\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny suggestions to help or should I just wait for a patch?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Found the solution myself. When you change the UI Scale you must restart the game to fix the issue I stated above. For example: When you begin the game your UI scale is set to 100%. If you change the UI scale to, for example, 80% the map indicators(apoapsis, periapsis, planets, ect...)\u00A0will be in the wrong locations. After restarting though, the map indicators will return to their correct positions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-26T00:20:07Z\u0022 title=\u002204/26/2016 12:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by lethalparadox0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFound solution\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}